to the editor an erosion of civil liberties editorial may 31 correctly points out that much of the bush administration 's response to sept 11 has been draconian and insensitive to fundamental constitutional values however attorney general john ashcroft 's decision to authorize federal bureau of investigation monitoring of the internet does not fall into this category many americans make the false assumption that internet communications are private and secure in fact expressing oneself on the internet is roughly equivalent to placing a sign in someone 's front yard the people who live there will probably see it but it is likely that many others will as well we must be wary of threats to our privacy but we must also be careful not to confuse the monitoring of public expression with eavesdropping on private channels david r dow houston may 31 2002 the writer is a professor at the university of houston law center

